# TypeScript

## Type System
- Enable strict mode
- Avoid `any` - use `unknown` for truly unknown types
- Prefer interfaces for objects, types for unions
- Use `readonly` for immutable properties

## Functions
- Always type parameters and return values
- Use optional parameters (`?`) not `| undefined`
- Use `void` for no return value

## Null Safety
- Enable `strictNullChecks`
- Use `?.` and `??` operators
- Prefer explicit checks over type assertions

## Generics
- Use meaningful names (not just `T`)
- Constrain with `extends` when needed
- Avoid over-engineering

## Utility Types
- `Partial<T>` for optional properties
- `Pick<T, K>` and `Omit<T, K>` for subsets
- `Record<K, V>` for key-value maps
- `ReturnType<T>` for function returns

## Avoid
- Type assertions (`as`) unless necessary
- `@ts-ignore` - fix the type issue
- Overly complex type gymnastics

